{"lemma":"دَعْوَةٌ","slug":"دَعْوَةٌ","root":"د.ع.#","root_slug":"د-ع-_","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ع-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دَعْوَة","root":"دعو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12618"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَعَا (daʕā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"],"examples":[{"text":"شُكْرًا عَلَى دَعْوَتِكَ لَنَا إِلَى الْمَقْهَى.","english":"Thank you for inviting us to the café."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"instance noun of دَعَا (daʕā)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"call; call to action","examples":[{"text":"عَارَضُوا دَعْوَتَهُ وَسَعَوْا لِقَتْلِهِ.","english":"They opposed his call and sought to kill him."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"invitation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"preaching, proselytization, evangelization, missionization","examples":[{"text":"لَهُۥ دَعْوَةُ ٱلْحَقِّ وَٱلَّذِينَ يَدْعُونَ مِن دُونِهِۦ لَا يَسْتَجِيبُونَ لَهُم بِشَيْءٍ إِلَّا كَبَـٰسِطِ كَفَّيْهِ إِلَى ٱلْمَاءِ لِيَبْلُغَ فَاهُ وَمَا هُوَ بِبَـٰلِغِهِۦ وَمَا دُعَاءُ ٱلْكَـٰفِرِينَ إِلَّا فِي ضَلَـٰلٍ","english":"To Him [alone] is the supplication of truth. And those they call upon besides Him do not respond to them with a thing, except as one who stretches his hands toward water [from afar, calling it] to reach his mouth, but it will not reach it [thus].1 And the supplication of the disbelievers is not but in error [i.e., futility]."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/daʕ.wa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12618","headword_ar":"دَعْوَةٌ","root":"dEw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as an inf. n. of un.] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single time"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of imprecation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is indicated in the S, and also, though less plainly, in the TA]. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duEaA='N","text_ar":"دُعَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Also, as such,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A call."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwamin~iY daEowapu Alr~ajula","text_ar":"هُوَمِنِّى دَعْوَةُ الرَّجُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkalobi","text_ar":"الكَلْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEowapa Alr~ajuli","text_ar":"دَعْوَةَ الرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkalobi","text_ar":"الكَلْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the former case"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dEwp","text_ar":"دعوة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being used as a simple subst., and in the latter case as an adv. n., (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadoru maA bayoniY wabayonahu *aAka","text_ar":"قَدْرُ مَا بَيْنِى وَبَيْنَهُ ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, is distant from me the space of the call of the man"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the dog"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahumu Ald~aEowapu EalaY","text_ar":"لَهُمُ الدَّعْوَةُ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayorihimo","text_ar":"غَيْرِهِمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The call is to them before the others of them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA: ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabodaA^u","text_ar":"يَبْدَاُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yubodaA^u","text_ar":"يُبْدَاُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) accord. to the T and the Nh, in the case of gifts, or pay, or salary. (TA.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"call to prayer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aEuwapu fiY AlHaba$api","text_ar":"الدَّعُوَةُ فِى الحَبَشَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The office of calling to prayer rests among the Abyssinians"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (JM, TA;) said by the Prophet in preference of his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^a*~in","text_ar":"مُوَذِّن"},{"kind":"text","text":"Bilál. (JM.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A call,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an invitation, to El-Islám."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoEuwka bidaEowapi AlA_isolaAmi","text_ar":"اَدْعُوكَ بِدَعْوَةِ الاـِسْلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlslAm","text_ar":"السلام"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diEaAyapi","text_ar":"دِعَايَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAslAm","text_ar":"الاسلام"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAEiyapi","text_ar":"دَاعِيَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I call thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"invite thee, by the declaration of the faith whereby the people of false religions are called:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAEiyapN","text_ar":"دَاعِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being an inf. n. syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEowapN","text_ar":"دَعْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAfiyapN","text_ar":"عَافِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibapN","text_ar":"عَاقِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (JM:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEowapu AlA_isolaAmi","text_ar":"دَعْوَةُ الاـِسْلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEAyatuhu","text_ar":"دَعايَتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAEiyatuhu","text_ar":"دَاعِيَتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEowapu AlHaq~i","text_ar":"دَعْوَةُ الحَقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in like manner] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the declaration that there is no deity but God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An invitation to food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and to beverage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Lh, specially"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a repast, feast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"banquet, on the occasion of a wedding"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) thus pronounced by most of the Arabs, except 'Adee of Er-Rabáb, who pronounce it, in this sense, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diEowapN","text_ar":"دِعْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A 'Obeyd, S, M, Msb:) it is an inf. n. in this sense, (S,) or a simple subst.: (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duEowapN","text_ar":"دُعْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; (K;) or, as some say, this, which is given as on the authority of Ktr, is a mistake: (TA:) and so does ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madoEaApN","text_ar":"مَدْعَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. an inf. n.]. (S, Msb, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kun~aAfiY","text_ar":"كُنَّافِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEowapi fulaAnK","text_ar":"دَعْوَةِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madoEaAtihi","text_ar":"مَدْعَاتِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We were"},{"kind":"text","text":"included"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the invitation"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duEaA='","text_ar":"دُعَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see 1])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such a one to food:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb: [but in the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naHonu","text_ar":"نَحْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kun~aA","text_ar":"كُنَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we were at the repast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"banquet, of such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] you say [also]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEaAhu A_ilaY Ald~aEowapi","text_ar":"دَعَاهُ اـِلَى الدَّعْوَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY AlmadoEaApi","text_ar":"الى المَدْعَاةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He invited him to the repast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"banquet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in this sense"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEowap","text_ar":"دَعْوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is commonly used in the present day]. (MA.) ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diEowapN","text_ar":"دِعْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b7-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEowaY","text_ar":"دَعْوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b8-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalifN","text_ar":"حَلِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalofN","text_ar":"حَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(accord. to different copies of the K) [both in the sense of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Confederation to aid"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assist"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) [whence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEowapN fulaAnK fiY baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"دَعْوَةٌ فُلَانٍ فِى بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The confederation of such a one is with the sons of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","JM","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}